Feature: the canonical lead CLAUDE.md primer defines the effectively-empty / no-product-defined repo detection signal as a two-signal test so a freshly bootstrapped lead can recognize that no product has been shaped yet

  lead-vglj (P2) — product authority 2026-06-29 (verbatim): "for the lead to
  detect when the repo is effectively empty and start a product discovery
  conversation with the user to start determining the shape of the new system."

  This scenario pins the DETECTION half. SCOPE PINNED 2026-06-30 (product
  authority, David): EFFECTIVELY EMPTY is a TWO-SIGNAL test — BOTH signals must
  hold: (1) no product-bearing bead in the beads registry, AND (2) no
  product-bearing scenario in the "features/" tree. The bootstrap scaffold —
  canonical-managed files, "CLAUDE.md", the typed ".claude/" files, the role
  templates, the placeholder shop primer, and the initialized-but-empty beads
  registry — is IGNORED by the test and does not by itself defeat either signal.
  Briefs and PDRs are NOT part of the two-signal test.

  The detection signal feeds the proactive-initiation trigger, the re-fire
  cadence, and the brainstorm-then-branch opener pinned by the sibling
  product-discovery scenarios in this family.

  AUTHORING ONLY — no BC dispatch. @bc tag is the Architect's to apply at
  assignment time; @lead_integration:templates below is provisional placement
  matching sibling primer-furniture scenarios.

